  "prompt": "What is a speech?",
  "response": "A speech is a formal or structured presentation or address given by an individual to an audience. It is a means of communication in which the speaker conveys information, shares ideas or opinions, or persuades or inspires others. Speeches can be delivered on various occasions, including public events, ceremonies, conferences, or political rallies. They can be prepared and rehearsed in advance or delivered impromptu. Effective speeches are well-organized, clear, engaging, and tailored to the audience and the purpose of the occasion.",
